race.comment: The Jessie Bazan yard has a big claim on this. Sticking with the senior rider of the two stablemates in COOL HEART (5). Has been racing well including a last start win and off the inside will stalk the pace and be looking for clear air in the straight. Going well and will be winding up late. Stablemate JEHBENTI (2) looks a great chance here fresh on the back of a recent trial win. Has the claimer aboard but the outside gate to overcome. Likely to be beaten for speed this trip but charge out wide late. GEE GEES ME BOY (6) has been three weeks between runs as he comes back from 1400m. Likely to also be beaten for speed but best form stacks up and will get home hard. ESPRIT DIVA (9) has been running on hard recently and is darn for a good run with cover. Gets chance to feature. ALPINE THUNDER (3) goes well fresh and can give a sight with the light weight.
